datasets.name: 1d8e639a
datasets.query:
with query_history as 
(SELECT
statement_id,
executed_by,
statement_text,
account_id, 
workspace_id, 
warehouse_id,
execution_status,
f.statement_type,
client_application,
COALESCE(error_message, 'None') AS error_message,
COALESCE(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS QueryRuntimeSeconds,
COALESCE(try_divide(total_task_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS CPUTotalExecutionTime,
COALESCE(try_divide(execution_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS ExecutionQueryTime,
COALESCE(try_divide(compilation_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS CompilationQueryTime,
COALESCE(try_divide(waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS QueueQueryTime,
COALESCE(try_divide(waiting_for_compute_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS StartUpQueryTime,
COALESCE(try_divide(result_fetch_duration_ms, 1000), 0) AS ResultFetchTime,
start_time,
end_time,
update_time,
COALESCE(read_bytes, 0) AS read_bytes,
COALESCE(read_io_cache_percent, 0) AS read_io_cache_percent,
from_result_cache,
COALESCE(spilled_local_bytes, 0) AS spilled_local_bytes,
COALESCE(total_task_duration_ms / total_duration_ms, NULL) AS TotalCPUTime_To_Execution_Time_Ratio, 
COALESCE(waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms / total_duration_ms, 0) AS ProportionQueueTime,
AVG(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000))  OVER () AS WarehouseAvgQueryRuntime,
AVG(try_divide(waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms, 1000)) OVER () AS WarehouseAvgQueueTime,
AVG(COALESCE(try_divide(waiting_at_capacity_duration_ms, 1000) / try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000), 0)) OVER () AS WarehouseAvgProportionTimeQueueing,
SUM(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000)) OVER () AS TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse,
SUM(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000)) OVER (PARTITION BY statement_text) AS TotalStatementTextTimeUsed, -- for query level aggregates
try_divide(try_divide(total_duration_ms, 1000) , TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse) AS ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery ,-- Can use this to chargeback (as long as you know denominator is only USED task time, not including idele time)
CASE WHEN read_bytes > 0 THEN try_divide(read_bytes,(1024*1024*1024))ELSE 0 END AS ReadDataAmountInGB,
CASE WHEN read_io_cache_percent > 0 THEN 'Used Cache' ELSE 'No Cache' END AS UsedCacheFlag,
CASE WHEN spilled_local_bytes > 0 THEN 'Spilled Data To Disk' ELSE 'No Spill' END AS HasSpillFlag,
CASE WHEN read_bytes > 0 THEN 'Did Read Data' ELSE 'No Data Read' END AS ReadDataFlag,
CASE WHEN CPUTotalExecutionTime > 0 THEN 'UsedWorkerTasks' ELSE 'NoWorkers' END AS UsedWorkerTasksFlag,
CASE WHEN spilled_local_bytes > 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS Calc_HasSpillFlag,
CASE WHEN read_bytes > 0 THEN 0.25 ELSE 0 END AS Calc_ReadDataFlag,
CASE WHEN CPUTotalExecutionTime > 0 THEN 0.25 ELSE 0 END AS Calc_UsedWorkerTasksFlag,
substr(statement_text, INSTR(statement_text, '/*') + 2, INSTR(statement_text, '*/') - INSTR(statement_text, '/*') - 2) AS dbt_metadata_json
FROM system.query.history f
WHERE warehouse_id = :warehouse_id
AND start_time > date_add(current_date(), -7) 
AND statement_type IS NOT NULL)

select to_date(start_time) as start_date, 
    DATE_TRUNC('hour', start_time) AS start_hour,
    workspace_id, 
    account_id, 
    warehouse_id, 
    avg(queryRuntimeSeconds), 
    avg(resultFetchTime), 
    avg(queueQueryTime), 
    percentile(queryRuntimeSeconds, 0.95) p95queryRuntimeSeconds, 
    percentile(queryRuntimeSeconds, 0.5) p50queryRuntimeSeconds

from query_history
group by all

datasets.name: 43fec0b8
datasets.query:
with usage as (
    SELECT
  --   u.record_id,
  u.account_id, 
  u.cloud, 
  u.workspace_id,
  u.sku_name,
  c.cluster_id,
  c.cluster_name,
  c.owned_by,
  c.driver_node_type,
  c.worker_node_type,
  c.min_autoscale_workers,
  c.max_autoscale_workers,
  c.auto_termination_minutes,
  c.dbr_version,
  --   c.change_time,
  --   u.usage_start_time,
--   u.usage_date,
  sum(u.usage_quantity) as dbus
FROM
  system.billing.usage u
  left outer JOIN system.compute.clusters c
  JOIN (
    SELECT
      u.record_id,
      c.cluster_id,
      max(c.change_time) change_time
    FROM
      system.billing.usage u
      JOIN system.compute.clusters c
    WHERE
      u.usage_metadata.cluster_id is not null
      and u.usage_start_time >= '2023-01-01'
      and u.usage_metadata.cluster_id = c.cluster_id
      and date_trunc('HOUR', c.change_time) <= date_trunc('HOUR', u.usage_start_time)
    GROUP BY
      all
  ) config
WHERE
  u.usage_metadata.cluster_id is not null
  and u.usage_start_time >= '2023-01-01' 
  and u.usage_date > date_add(current_date(), -30 )
  and u.usage_metadata.cluster_id = c.cluster_id
  and u.record_id = config.record_id
  and c.cluster_id = config.cluster_id
  and c.change_time = config.change_time
  and u.sku_name ilike '%all_purpose%'
group by
  all 
), 
top_clusters as 
(
    SELECT
  account_id, 
  cloud, 
  workspace_id,
  sku_name,
  cluster_id,
  cluster_name,
  owned_by,
  driver_node_type,
  worker_node_type,
  min_autoscale_workers,
  max_autoscale_workers,
  auto_termination_minutes,
  dbr_version,
  --   c.change_time,
  --   u.usage_start_time,
  dbus,
  rank(sum(dbus)) over(partition by account_id, cloud, workspace_id order by sum(dbus) desc) rnk, 
  rank(sum(dbus)) over(partition by account_id, cloud order by sum(dbus) desc) rnk_overall 
    -- rank(sum(dbus)) over(order by dbus DESC) as rnk_overall, 
FROM usage
group by all 
)
select * 
from top_clusters 
where rnk < :top_n

datasets.name: 8dab1378
datasets.query:
with monthly_usage as 
(SELECT
  account_id, 
  cloud, 
  workspace_id,
  sku_name,
  trunc(usage_date, 'MM') as monthStart,
  billing_origin_product,
  sum(usage_quantity) as dbus
FROM
  system.billing.usage
WHERE
  trunc(usage_date, 'MM') > trunc(add_months(current_date(), - :loookback_months), 'MM')
  AND usage_unit = 'DBU'
group by all ),
mom_growth as
(select account_id, 
  cloud, 
  workspace_id,
  monthStart,
  dbus, 
  lag(dbus,1) over(partition by account_id, cloud, workspace_id, sku_name, billing_origin_product order by monthStart) as previous_dbus, 
  dbus - previous_dbus as dbus_change,
  try_divide(dbus_change,previous_dbus) as pct_change
from monthly_usage)

select account_id, 
  cloud, 
  workspace_id,
  sum(dbus) dbus,
  avg(pct_change) as avg_mom_growth
from mom_growth
group by all

datasets.name: c544593a
datasets.query:
SELECT
  account_id,
  workspace_id,
  warehouse_id,
  SUM(TIMESTAMPDIFF(MINUTE, start_time, end_time)) / 60.0 AS uptime_hours
FROM
  (
    SELECT
      account_id,
      workspace_id,
      starting.warehouse_id,
      starting.event_time AS start_time,
      (
        SELECT
          MIN(stopping.event_time)
        FROM
          system.compute.warehouse_events AS stopping
        WHERE
          stopping.warehouse_id = starting.warehouse_id
          AND stopping.event_type = 'STOPPED'
          AND stopping.event_time > starting.event_time
      ) AS end_time
    FROM
      system.compute.warehouse_events AS starting
    WHERE
      starting.event_type = 'STARTING' --   AND MONTH(starting.event_time) = 7
      --   AND YEAR(starting.event_time) = YEAR(CURRENT_DATE())
      and starting.event_time > date_add(current_date(), -30)
  ) AS warehouse_uptime
WHERE
  end_time IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY
  all
ORDER BY
  uptime_hours DESC
